            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A goods transport agency issues a consignment note and takes responsibility for the goods in transit, while a transporter that only supplies a vehicle without a consignment note is not a GTA. That document decides the tax: GTA services attract 5% under reverse or forward charge, whereas road transport of goods by a non-GTA is exempt."
          }
